Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.00,0:05:46.50,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,jugon
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.68,0:06:44.14,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Toshimi Ebihara (27)\NSaori's Childhood Friend\NDaughter of the Head of the Fishermen's Union
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.41,0:07:01.91,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Rokuro Fukuyama (28)\NSaori's Childhood Friend\NFisherman
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.68,0:08:09.31,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikoto Shimabukuro (130)\NLady Mikoto
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.64,0:09:36.15,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Benzo Kadowaki (52)\NSaori's Father\NFisherman
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.70,0:16:01.16,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,The Next Day\NEbihara House
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.22,0:02:06.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.08,0:02:07.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd better see some gratitude, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.86,0:02:09.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You showed up without so much as calling ahead,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.64,0:02:11.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,telling me to join you on this stupid trip to Fukui,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.78,0:02:14.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and out of the kindness of my heart I agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.80,0:02:18.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, don't be so crabby. I'm paying for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.95,0:02:22.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So? Where're we headed, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.10,0:02:26.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A tiny island named Bikuni Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.20,0:02:28.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But most of the locals call it...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.66,0:02:31.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the island where the mermaid lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.75,0:02:34.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mermaid?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.29,0:02:35.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.82,0:02:37.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.38,0:02:39.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That letter you got asking us to find the mermaid...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.33,0:02:42.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't just some idiot who wants to see one, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.60,0:02:44.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.61,0:02:48.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There was only one line,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.75,0:02:50.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,written in shaky handwriting...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.34,0:02:55.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The mermaid is going to kill me! Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.51,0:02:57.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The mermaid...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.36,0:02:58.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...is going to kill me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.74,0:03:07.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Saori Kadowaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.28,0:03:11.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Three days ago, she stopped coming in to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.12,0:03:16.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Three days ago... That's around the time I got the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.14,0:03:20.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Her neighbors think she took a boat to the mainland.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.30,0:03:22.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.05,0:03:23.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, right, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.53,0:03:26.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, gotta get ready for the festival!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.86,0:03:28.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.23,0:03:33.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The annual Dugong Festival is today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.39,0:03:39.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to know more, try the souvenir shop on the corner. That's where Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.54,0:03:41.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A lucky mermaid charm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.98,0:03:43.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,a mermaid cell phone strap...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.02,0:03:46.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and special dugong buns...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.05,0:03:49.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This island's full of mermaids, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.75,0:03:52.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Arrow of Dugong?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.19,0:03:55.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... It's an amulet for immortality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.01,0:03:59.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Only three are given away each year,\Nat the annual Dugong Festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.38,0:04:06.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} won an arrow at last year's festival, but she lost it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.94,0:04:09.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was terrified that the mermaid would curse her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.46,0:04:12.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mermaids, yeah right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.27,0:04:13.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But mermaids do exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.60,0:04:15.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Naoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.72,0:04:21.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, Lady Mikoto ate the flesh of a mermaid and received immortality.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.95,0:04:28.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Arrow of Dugong has her hair tied to it, and anyone who wins one can become immortal!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.73,0:04:35.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not surprised Saori ran away from the island after she lost her arrow. She could be cursed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.72,0:04:37.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And she is...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.99,0:04:40.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Naoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, a childhood friend of Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.48,0:04:43.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And who's this Lady Mikoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.23,0:04:47.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The head of the festival and matriarch of the Shimabukuro family.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.14,0:04:49.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's the icon of the island!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.85,0:04:53.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How old is this lady, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.58,0:04:58.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. I've heard rumors that she's 100 or 200 years old...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.93,0:05:02.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,200 years old? No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.78,0:05:06.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My great-grandmother is exactly 130 years old this year!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.19,0:05:08.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can check her birth certificate if you like!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.02,0:05:11.29,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's old enough for the Guinness Book of World Records.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.91,0:05:16.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So where is yer old lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.51,0:05:20.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's in her room, blessing the three arrows that are going to be handed out at the festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.88,0:05:24.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then Lady Mikoto really {\i1}did{\i0} eat mermaid's flesh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.20,0:05:25.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.30,0:05:32.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mermaids don't exist, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.73,0:05:35.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But the Arrow of Dugong...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.80,0:05:40.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My late mother told me it was originally the Arrow of Jugon, an amulet to ward off evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.00,0:05:42.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When Great-Grandma started getting attention for her long life,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.34,0:05:46.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,people around here renamed it the Arrow of Dugong!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.95,0:05:49.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mother passed away?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.67,0:05:50.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.66,0:05:52.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Five years ago, with my father, at sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.32,0:05:54.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My grandparents were lost at sea too before I was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.60,0:05:58.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Great-Grandma and I are the only members of the family left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.30,0:06:01.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe there's somethin' to the legends!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.34,0:06:04.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.26,0:06:08.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I went to the mainland with Saori just a few days ago and nothing happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.84,0:06:09.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.41,0:06:10.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were with Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.76,0:06:11.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.45,0:06:13.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Four days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.65,0:06:17.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I went to the dentist and she came along.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.09,0:06:20.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have a dentist on the island, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.70,0:06:23.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What state was she in when you saw her?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.45,0:06:26.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was terrified because she'd lost that arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.76,0:06:28.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm cursed by the mermaid!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.35,0:06:32.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She wouldn't believe the curse wasn't real.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.96,0:06:34.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Silly...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.97,0:06:38.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You just don't believe in Lady Mikoto's powers, do you, Kimie?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.77,0:06:40.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Toshimi...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.09,0:06:44.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's the real deal! She really ate the flesh of a mermaid!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.78,0:06:49.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We even found a mermaid's corpse three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.70,0:06:51.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A mermaid's corpse?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.32,0:06:52.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough, Toshimi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.44,0:06:54.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Rokuro...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.39,0:06:57.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got nothing more to say to outsiders.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.89,0:07:00.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're looking for Saori,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.54,0:07:02.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,why're you wasting time here?\NJust go to her house.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.22,0:07:07.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's if that drunk father of hers lets you in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.20,0:07:11.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A girl's gone missing, and nobody's freakin' out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.04,0:07:14.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Saori fights with her dad and runs away all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.27,0:07:18.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you take us to Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.47,0:07:21.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, after the festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.90,0:07:24.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of festival is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.50,0:07:27.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,People buy tickets,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.62,0:07:29.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and if the number on the ticket matches the number Great-Grandma draws,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.81,0:07:31.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,they win an Arrow of Dugong.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.60,0:07:34.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We call it a festival, but it's more like a lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.59,0:07:36.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.08,0:07:38.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you two give it a go?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.60,0:07:43.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,An elderly couple cancelled their ticket order this morning, so I've got two extra.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.70,0:07:48.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you say so...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.65,0:07:58.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.34,0:07:59.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.85,0:08:11.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's Lady Mikoto...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.50,0:08:14.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's so tiny...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.70,0:08:17.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just an old lady in lotsa make-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.19,0:08:26.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-She...set fire to the paper screens!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.48,0:08:29.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The fire is taking the shape of words!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.87,0:08:44.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.28,0:08:47.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The winning numbers are under the screens!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.81,0:08:50.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! I won!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.08,0:08:52.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hooray! I'm so lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.34,0:08:54.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,R-R-Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.86,0:08:56.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.40,0:08:58.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I won!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.02,0:09:05.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Attention, winners.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.93,0:09:10.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The time has come to bestow the Arrows of Dugong.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.20,0:09:11.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please follow me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.68,0:09:12.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to the Waterfall of the Mermaid!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.63,0:09:21.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Will the three fortunate ones please come forth?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.97,0:09:23.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.20,0:09:25.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes, yes, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.95,0:09:29.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One more!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.59,0:09:31.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there one more winner here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.14,0:09:34.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.62,0:09:37.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.55,0:09:38.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Weird...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.90,0:09:41.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that girl won.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.72,0:09:45.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, and I don't see her around.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.13,0:09:48.38,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But we soon found her...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.38,0:09:50.75,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}at the foot of the waterfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.55,0:09:54.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,May fortune light the path for these three!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.32,0:10:01.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.94,0:10:03.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.17,0:10:22.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Toshimi?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.86,0:10:24.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.59,0:10:26.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Or did somebody...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.28,0:10:28.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It might not be either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.00,0:10:32.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the rope that strangled Toshimi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.17,0:10:35.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's part of the rope fence we strung here to keep people from falling in the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.34,0:10:37.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.35,0:10:40.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.90,0:10:45.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} fell into the river in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.63,0:10:53.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She grabbed the rope, but the stake slipped out of the mud and the rope wrapped around her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.20,0:10:55.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But doesn't it seem fishy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.99,0:10:59.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The festival was still goin' on at the foot of the waterfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.71,0:11:02.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So why'd she go wanderin' into the woods?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.30,0:11:05.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she was looking for the mermaid's grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.56,0:11:06.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.17,0:11:09.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a mermaid's grave somewhere in this forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.50,0:11:12.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It contains the bones of the mermaid who was found three years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.84,0:11:18.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,on the night of the festival, when the shrine's warehouse burned down.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.07,0:11:21.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Toshimi was always curious about that grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.90,0:11:23.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on just a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.28,0:11:24.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You keep talkin' about mermaid this and mermaid that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.66,0:11:26.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't {\i1}really{\i0} a mermaid, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.96,0:11:28.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.45,0:11:30.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what the islanders believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.75,0:11:34.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the police from the mainland thought it was the body of a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.39,0:11:38.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How could it be an ordinary woman? The bones only went down to the waist!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.72,0:11:40.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They did?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.72,0:11:45.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A couple of large pillars in the warehouse had crushed the body from the waist down.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.55,0:11:48.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But then we moved the pillars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.26,0:11:50.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The leg bones that should've been on the other side of the pillars...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.25,0:11:52.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...weren't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.38,0:11:56.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the police thought it was a woman's body, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.34,0:11:57.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.41,0:12:01.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They said a disgruntled tourist must've broken into the warehouse
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.06,0:12:04.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,looking for an extra arrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.59,0:12:08.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,lit a candle, and accidentally started a fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.11,0:12:14.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After a year passed without anyone claiming the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.23,0:12:16.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,we decided to give it a proper burial.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.81,0:12:20.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we ran into another problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.05,0:12:21.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.31,0:12:22.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Grave robbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.05,0:12:29.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid tourists started trying to dig up the body and steal the bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.61,0:12:35.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So Great-Grandmother had someone move the grave to a secret spot in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.25,0:12:40.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, whether this was murder, suicide or accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.70,0:12:45.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,we can't do anything but take Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} down and wait for the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.37,0:12:53.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If it was murder, Toshimi was asking for trouble, coming up here alone in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.85,0:12:57.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a thing to say about your fiancée!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.20,0:12:59.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Fiancée?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.99,0:13:02.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Our parents arranged that without our consent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.84,0:13:04.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't my choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.57,0:13:08.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And now my mom and dad are dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.73,0:13:11.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Toshimi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.21,0:13:13.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Toshimi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.44,0:13:15.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Toshimi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.59,0:13:16.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.25,0:13:21.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Toshimi's father, Ebihara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.\NHe's head of the local fishermen's union.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.40,0:13:23.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.25,0:13:26.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, did you contact the Fukui prefectural police?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.82,0:13:31.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but they won't be able to come out for a while. The sea's too rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.84,0:13:33.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, for the love of...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.22,0:13:35.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Great! This is perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.29,0:13:39.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It means the killer's gotta stay put on the island!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.70,0:13:41.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Killer, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.46,0:13:44.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't even decided if this was murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.57,0:13:46.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.75,0:13:48.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,An inner tube?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.20,0:13:54.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Heiji-{\i1}niichan{\i0} and I found it stuck in the river, between the waterfall and the river mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.08,0:13:56.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm guessin' our culprit knocked Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} out at the top of the waterfall,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.93,0:14:00.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,wrapped the rope around her neck,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.15,0:14:02.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,an' floated her down the river to fake a hangin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.30,0:14:06.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was last seen at the shrine two hours before her body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.87,0:14:10.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It takes less'n an hour to climb to the top of the waterfall an' back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.25,0:14:15.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There was plenty of time for {\i1}anyone{\i0} to kill her an' make it look like an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.88,0:14:19.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the killer is still somewhere on this island!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.61,0:14:26.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's taking the old lady so long?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.27,0:14:29.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said she'll come down to answer questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.41,0:14:32.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but she's tired from the festival, so she might not stay long.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.73,0:14:36.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.57,0:14:47.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the ones who wanted to see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.20,0:14:50.04,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Without her make-up, she's an ogre!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.04,0:14:52.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.17,0:14:56.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was wondering how you chose the winning numbers...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.73,0:14:59.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Er...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.85,0:15:01.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At random.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.64,0:15:06.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For a while, I picked the winning numbers from the horse races!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.27,0:15:08.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.04,0:15:13.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why're ya so stingy with the arrows? You oughta give away more than three!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.58,0:15:15.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.55,0:15:19.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I only have so much hair on my head to tie to the arrows.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.60,0:15:23.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Great-Grandma! Your bath's ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.68,0:15:30.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. If that's all, I'd like to take my bath and go to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.62,0:15:32.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! I still have a quest—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.29,0:15:34.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You there... Young girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.24,0:15:37.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The one with your hair tied back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.71,0:15:38.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.34,0:15:42.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Arrow of Dugong is a charm to ward off evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.73,0:15:45.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let go of it, and evil will fall upon you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.72,0:15:50.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Men will return to dust and become heartless devils.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.05,0:15:54.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Women will return to water and become speechless mermaids.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.13,0:15:58.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ever let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.59,0:16:04.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't ya glad we brought our school uniforms?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.93,0:16:08.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are ya sure we're supposed to be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.80,0:16:12.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't sweat it! It's the perfect chance to snoop around!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.44,0:16:21.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You came too, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.64,0:16:23.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Er... Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.31,0:16:29.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Kadowaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't go home yesterday. Did you see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.53,0:16:33.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, but I heard he was picking fights with tourists at the local tavern.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.63,0:16:37.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Drinkin' all night, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.85,0:16:38.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.85,0:16:43.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see Naoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.\NHer name was in the guestbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.06,0:16:45.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Naoko here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.11,0:16:56.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}? You afraid of thunder?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.90,0:16:58.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.46,0:16:59.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's someone outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.16,0:17:04.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.82,0:17:06.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.01,0:17:07.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Heiji...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.20,0:17:09.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's someone outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.01,0:17:09.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.67,0:17:13.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.10,0:17:31.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's been dead less than an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.35,0:17:36.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The footprints on the sand are from sandals and boots.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.04,0:17:38.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Naoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was probably wearin' guest sandals from the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.28,0:17:40.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so the boots must belong to the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.41,0:17:42.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would anyone do this to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.36,0:17:43.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's your answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.48,0:17:48.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look. Somebody stepped on an Arrow of Dugong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.09,0:17:50.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from the sandal prints,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.03,0:17:52.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Naoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} must've dropped it and stepped on it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.35,0:17:54.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,while she was struggling with the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.35,0:17:57.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the killer was after the arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.40,0:18:03.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if we follow the boot prints, we'll find the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.37,0:18:04.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.81,0:18:07.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey... The prints...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.85,0:18:10.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...go straight into the sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.31,0:18:12.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.79,0:18:17.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something shiny around the prints.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.44,0:18:19.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.11,0:18:23.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.39,0:18:25.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Scales...from a fish?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.95,0:18:30.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a couple scales on Naoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s clothes too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.81,0:18:31.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.99,0:18:32.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.14,0:18:36.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.40,0:18:38.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Investigating the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.80,0:18:41.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the job of the Fukui Police!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.86,0:18:42.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Police?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.89,0:18:45.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you've finally made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.85,0:18:47.05,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}After that,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.05,0:18:49.34,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}the police searched everybody at the funeral,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.34,0:18:52.54,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}to see if the killer who stole Naoko{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s arrow was still among us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.46,0:18:54.88,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But the only people with arrows
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.88,0:18:58.35,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}were Benzo{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10} and Kazuha, who'd won them at the festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.82,0:19:02.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kudo. Got any leads?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.02,0:19:03.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.87,0:19:07.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All I've noticed is that Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Naoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the two confirmed victims,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.05,0:19:09.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who's missing,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.42,0:19:13.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,all believed in Lady Mikoto's powers
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.53,0:19:16.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and were obsessed with the Arrow of Dugong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.73,0:19:19.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. {\i1}Too{\i0} obsessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.85,0:19:24.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If we only knew who had which ticket at last night's festival...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.93,0:19:26.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.50,0:19:30.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We have everyone sign a list.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.62,0:19:33.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to come with me now and have a look at the list?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.61,0:19:34.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.41,0:19:36.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Careful there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.89,0:19:39.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez... Pull yourself together, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.70,0:19:41.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kimie...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.20,0:19:45.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know this isn't the best time...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.04,0:19:47.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but have you thought about what I said?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.35,0:19:49.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm serious, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.04,0:19:50.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.15,0:19:52.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not after Toshimi's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.15,0:19:58.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And I can't leave this island and abandon Great-Grandma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.95,0:20:00.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.17,0:20:06.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So all five of you went to school together, even college?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.97,0:20:08.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.23,0:20:10.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We were all big movie fans,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.02,0:20:12.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so in college we joined the film club,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.97,0:20:16.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and made our own film, The Legend of Bikuni!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.06,0:20:21.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When it won the gold medal at a film festival, we were so excited!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.40,0:20:23.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We were ready to go to Hollywood!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.88,0:20:25.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.56,0:20:30.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But in the end, none of us could forget the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.50,0:20:33.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who would have thought Toshimi and Naoko would end up like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.98,0:20:35.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh, that's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.35,0:20:39.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure I kept it here...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.36,0:20:41.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it there?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.10,0:20:42.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gone... Just this year's.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.76,0:20:46.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the ol' lady took it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.17,0:20:47.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.91,0:20:50.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who else knew the entry books were here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.70,0:20:53.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Most of the locals, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.56,0:20:57.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll look through the other rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.08,0:21:01.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me help you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.07,0:21:02.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Me too...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.22,0:21:03.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.55,0:21:11.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.63,0:21:13.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The old foreign minister...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.00,0:21:14.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the director of the Secretariat...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.34,0:21:15.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the president of the Bank of Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.75,0:21:18.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess they all wanted to live forever...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.00,0:21:21.01,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Shiho Miyano?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.01,0:21:25.20,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Isn't that... {\i1}her{\i0} real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.37,0:21:27.65,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Nah, it can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.65,0:21:30.50,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}She's not the type who'd care about eternal youth and beauty...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.02,0:21:35.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.71,0:21:39.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We just saw her! A woman with light hair and glasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.91,0:21:41.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was starin' at us!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.14,0:21:44.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.44,0:21:46.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.03,0:21:47.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.11,0:21:49.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She said she was going to look through the new warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.72,0:21:51.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the warehouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.60,0:21:54.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She said it was behind the shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.31,0:21:57.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, check out that glow!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.25,0:21:58.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It couldn't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.16,0:22:01.77,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The warehouse kept burning through the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.48,0:22:05.16,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It burned to the ground, just like it did three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.53,0:22:11.45,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yes, just like three years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.45,0:22:13.45,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}there was a body inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.58,0:22:18.33,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Half a Day Later
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.76,0:22:17.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I see... Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.02,0:22:22.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? How'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.04,0:22:27.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They compared the teeth of the burnt body with Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s dental records.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.68,0:22:29.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They were a perfect match.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.30,0:22:31.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.30,0:22:32.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.85,0:22:36.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not true...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.25,0:22:38.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.17,0:22:39.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be true!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.70,0:22:43.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.65,0:22:45.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So Kimie has died...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.89,0:22:47.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, ol' lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.89,0:22:49.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer swooped in the minute we took our eyes off her.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.89,0:22:53.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Another innocent young life snuffed out...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.00,0:22:56.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,while an old fool like me lives on...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.85,0:23:01.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, remember when you moved the mermaid's grave?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.68,0:23:03.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who did it for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.81,0:23:05.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.61,0:23:09.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That person has left this world as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.32,0:23:14.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.15,0:23:17.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Found anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.09,0:23:18.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.69,0:23:21.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of case is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.05,0:23:24.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have a suspect or a motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.50,0:23:26.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.97,0:23:28.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.82,0:23:31.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone just called Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s place,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.19,0:23:32.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the person on the other end said something weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.54,0:23:33.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something weird?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.85,0:23:36.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much for selling us the arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.53,0:23:40.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was well worth the million yen. Our son's operation was a success!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.83,0:23:42.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They bought an arrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.43,0:23:43.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For a million yen?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.85,0:23:50.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They said a man who worked at the shrine sold it to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.44,0:23:55.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet it was that old couple who cancelled their tickets on the morning of the festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.80,0:23:57.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.05,0:23:58.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But who was the guy who sold them the arrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.95,0:24:00.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't know his name,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.46,0:24:03.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but they said he was a big guy, about 50 years old, with a stubby beard.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.80,0:24:04.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.35,0:24:06.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Benzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.81,0:24:14.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Benzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left last night right after we did?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.17,0:24:16.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He went running out, looking pale.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.85,0:24:19.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like I thought. Benzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} overheard us.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.42,0:24:24.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He heard us talkin' about goin' down to Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house to look at that notebook,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.77,0:24:27.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so he beat us there and stole it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.47,0:24:32.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} has died, I guess this year's Dugong Festival will be the last.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.80,0:24:34.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess so...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.42,0:24:37.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.76,0:24:42.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you show us again which footprints are yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.90,0:24:45.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.12,0:24:50.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.40,0:24:52.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.52,0:24:56.93,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A dent on the bottom of the sandal...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.93,0:24:58.29,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's still fresh...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.96,0:25:01.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha, lend me that arrow of yours, 'kay?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.25,0:25:08.60,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A perfect match.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.21,0:25:12.17,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is the sandal that stepped on the Arrow of Dugong on the sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.03,0:25:14.41,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.41,0:25:15.47,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's just like I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.44,0:25:21.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's Saori's room...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.75,0:25:27.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this bag?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.00,0:25:29.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.14,0:25:31.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.05,0:25:33.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Saori's run-away kit.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.81,0:25:37.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She usually just stayed over at Kimie's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.00,0:25:40.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She left clothes and an extra pair of glasses there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.48,0:25:44.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is there a photo of Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.17,0:25:45.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There should be a photo album somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.12,0:25:50.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, was this the person you saw in the garden?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.17,0:25:54.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. It was dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.02,0:25:59.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are these photos from the time you guys made your own movie about Bikuni?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.33,0:26:00.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.35,0:26:01.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.86,0:26:04.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is great!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.73,0:26:08.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It really looks like a mermaid's swimming in the sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.79,0:26:12.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... And this storm scene looks so real...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.87,0:26:15.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The movie won at the film festival
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.99,0:26:19.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,mostly because of Saori's visual effects and Kimie's special-effects make-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.00,0:26:22.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait a sec...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.68,0:26:29.76,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Her account book, bank card, name seal, driver's license and passport are all here,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.76,0:26:31.44,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}but I can't find one thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.44,0:26:33.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It couldn't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.39,0:26:35.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me...!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.40,0:26:44.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori here...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.34,0:26:48.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Kudo—I mean, old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.18,0:26:51.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect timing. I was just about to phone ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.51,0:26:55.00,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Remember the sandal prints on the beach?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.00,0:26:57.10,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I found a sandal with a dent mark\Nfrom stepping on an arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.47,0:26:59.55,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It proves the killer left the funeral room,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.55,0:27:02.69,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}walked out to the fishing net where Naoko{\rHonorifics - Radio\be10}-san{\r\be10} was waiting,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.69,0:27:05.64,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}killed her, then went back to the room again!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.29,0:27:11.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only two people who could've done that were Benzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and Rokuro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.10,0:27:14.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But seeing how upset Rokuro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was that afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.90,0:27:17.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I find it hard to believe he'd hurt Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.33,0:27:20.07,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Which means the killer's gotta be...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.95,0:27:25.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori, here's my deduction. Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.11,0:27:27.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.93,0:27:44.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot! That's crazy talk!\NI ain't gonna swallow that!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.11,0:27:46.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.46,0:27:48.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When you have eliminated the impossible,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.68,0:27:51.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,whatever remains, however improbable,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.14,0:27:54.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,must be the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.63,0:27:56.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.20,0:27:57.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.93,0:28:00.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We've located Benzo Kadowaki on the mountain! We're in pursuit!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.89,0:28:02.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. Let's go, men!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.60,0:28:06.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I'll hook up with ya after we arrest Benzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.29,0:28:07.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.05,0:28:08.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.85,0:28:14.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to believe it either, Hattori...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.70,0:28:16.96,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's not true! It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.96,0:28:18.75,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'm not buyin' it, Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.59,0:28:21.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.53,0:28:23.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You smell incense?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.42,0:28:24.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ya kiddin' me?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.72,0:28:26.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who'd burn incense up here on the...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.16,0:28:33.29,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Danger - Cliff Ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.70,0:28:36.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A grave...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.85,0:28:38.45,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The grave of that so-called mermaid...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hang on...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.92,0:28:41.29,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If that's the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.60,0:28:45.51,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The person Kudo fingered...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.51,0:28:48.21,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}really is the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.10,0:28:52.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The cliff!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.95,0:29:08.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.65,0:29:28.39,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}H...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.39,0:29:29.78,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Heiji...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.96,0:29:37.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on, Kazuha...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.01,0:29:39.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'll pull ya up in a sec...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.79,0:29:42.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.74,0:29:44.04,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The branch...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.04,0:29:46.04,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's gonna break...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.04,0:29:48.04,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}At this rate, both of us...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.58,0:29:53.66,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'm sorry, Heiji...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.66,0:29:55.80,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But you've gotta live...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.80,0:29:57.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}For both of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.95,0:29:59.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kazuha?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.56,0:30:01.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye-bye...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.41,0:30:03.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.28,0:30:18.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.42,0:30:22.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought you the guy you were asking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.21,0:30:26.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First, where's the kid from Osaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.92,0:30:30.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We lost track of him on the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.76,0:30:38.70,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}H-Heiji, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.70,0:30:41.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why didn't you let go?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.74,0:30:45.21,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}We'll both die if we stay like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.30,0:30:47.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let go of my hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.67,0:30:50.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.00,0:30:52.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't ya move!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.26,0:30:55.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If ya move, I'll kill ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.16,0:30:57.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Heiji...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.78,0:31:00.42,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What's wrong, Hattori?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.42,0:31:02.37,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why haven't you shown up?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.37,0:31:03.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What're you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.81,0:31:06.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon already! How long do we have to wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.30,0:31:08.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're busy people, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.72,0:31:16.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Lady Mikoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.55,0:31:19.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's Lady Mikoto doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.11,0:31:28.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then. Now that everybody's here, I'd better get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.15,0:31:31.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Time for the truth behind these three murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.99,0:31:36.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The first victim, Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was hanged from the Waterfall of the Mermaid.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.63,0:31:42.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The second victim, Naoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was strangled and entangled in a fishing net.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.92,0:31:47.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the third victim, Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, died in the warehouse fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.10,0:31:51.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To start, let's take a closer look at the {\i1}second{\i0} murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.35,0:31:53.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,From the situation at the crime scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.91,0:31:57.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it looks like the killer walked along the shore to get to and from the crime scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.66,0:32:01.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,with the footprints being washed away by the waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.39,0:32:05.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The footprints were a trick,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.44,0:32:10.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the killer really snuck in and out of the funeral hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.35,0:32:15.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the only people who could've snuck out of the funeral at that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.70,0:32:18.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...were Rokuro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Benzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.83,0:32:20.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It couldn't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.66,0:32:23.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me ask you something, Benzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.29,0:32:25.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On the morning of the festival,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.81,0:32:30.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you sold an Arrow of Dugong to an elderly couple for 1,000,000 yen, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.68,0:32:34.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. The arrow my daughter Saori won last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.91,0:32:37.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm her guardian, so I got every right to do what I want with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.69,0:32:41.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That 1,000,000 yen whetted your appetite for more money.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.48,0:32:45.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} won an arrow this year,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.34,0:32:48.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you lured her to the top of the waterfall and killed her to steal her winning ticket!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.03,0:32:51.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You put her body in an inner tube so it wouldn't get stuck in the river!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.56,0:32:52.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that wasn't all.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.50,0:32:55.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, Naoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who'd also won an arrow at the festival—
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.78,0:33:00.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you called her out on the night of the funeral, killed her and stole her arrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.51,0:33:03.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But if the records at the shrine were checked,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.55,0:33:06.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,everyone would find out that Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s ticket was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.45,0:33:11.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you went to Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house before we got there to steal the notebook,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.12,0:33:16.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} caught you, so you locked her in the warehouse and burned it down!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.34,0:33:21.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This notebook you had when we caught you is proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.53,0:33:24.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We found your fingerprints on that inner tube!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.74,0:33:27.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Benzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.68,0:33:30.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If Benzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were the killer,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.72,0:33:33.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he could've destroyed the notebook in the warehouse fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.15,0:33:38.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All the locals knew where to find the notebook anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.39,0:33:41.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think he'd have to rush over to steal it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.27,0:33:43.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What about his prints on the inner tube?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.80,0:33:48.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably found the ticket and the inner tube floating in the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.54,0:33:52.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He must've touched the inner tube while trying to pick up the ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.32,0:33:55.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, the detective's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.14,0:33:58.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I stole the notebook 'cause I was afraid everybody would think I was the killer
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.70,0:34:01.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,if they knew whose ticket I had.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.10,0:34:05.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Rokuro Fukuyama, {\i1}you{\i0} must be the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.72,0:34:07.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.24,0:34:09.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it wasn't him, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.90,0:34:11.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.23,0:34:14.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer used the inner tube trick to hang Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.73,0:34:19.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She'd float down the waterfall without getting caught on anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.40,0:34:21.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That way it would look like an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.85,0:34:23.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But being a fisherman, Rokuro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has very strong arms,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.81,0:34:26.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wasn't very heavy,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.09,0:34:29.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so it would have been easier for him to just toss her into the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.67,0:34:34.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He wouldn't have had to use an inner tube, which would only be left behind as evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.13,0:34:39.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But if neither of them is the killer, then who is?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.03,0:34:44.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer made it look like Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s death was an accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.46,0:34:48.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but made no attempt to hide the fact that Naoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.45,0:34:52.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what that means?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.49,0:34:56.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, uh... No, I don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.07,0:34:58.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.02,0:35:02.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the police didn't arrive right away because the sea was too rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.30,0:35:06.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, the police would have arrived sometime that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.17,0:35:07.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And since it was a case of murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.85,0:35:09.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the investigation would have been intense.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.45,0:35:11.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer wouldn't have been able to move about freely.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.79,0:35:14.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why it had to look like an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.93,0:35:21.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the killer planned to kill Naoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.72,0:35:27.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But no one would have known Naoko had won an arrow until she came forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.54,0:35:28.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.89,0:35:32.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer's motive wasn't to steal an arrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.67,0:35:35.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,nor was it to kill whoever won it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.67,0:35:42.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was only made to look that way to mislead the investigation!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.21,0:35:43.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.65,0:35:47.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason the killer made it obvious that Naoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.28,0:35:51.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was so that everyone's attention was on the scene of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.64,0:35:57.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer used that time to carry out the third murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.00,0:36:01.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer planned and executed each crime very carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.81,0:36:06.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't on a whim.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.12,0:36:10.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only person who could have prepared everything before the festival is...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.95,0:36:12.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.67,0:36:15.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone who knew beforehand
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.43,0:36:19.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that Toshimi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Naoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were going to win arrows.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.13,0:36:19.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.70,0:36:23.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer is you!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.48,0:36:28.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.95,0:36:33.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer is you, Lady Mikoto!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.65,0:36:40.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You've gotta be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.60,0:36:43.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How could someone who's 130 years old do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.76,0:36:46.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if she had an accomplice?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.28,0:36:47.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Accomplice?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.54,0:36:52.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If neither Rokuro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} nor Benzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} could have killed Naoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.53,0:36:55.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then the only other person who could have done it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.62,0:36:57.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.58,0:37:01.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.36,0:37:04.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kimie was the third victim!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.12,0:37:07.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if the victim in the warehouse fire wasn't Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.71,0:37:08.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.95,0:37:11.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} just told us she went to the dentist!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.20,0:37:15.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And those dental records matched the body...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.32,0:37:17.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You heard that too, didn't you, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.25,0:37:20.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said she went to the dentist...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.11,0:37:21.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.60,0:37:23.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She said she went to a dentist on the mainland with Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.99,0:37:25.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.99,0:37:27.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.21,0:37:30.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the one with the dental appointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.01,0:37:35.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went with Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to see the dentist on the mainland.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.58,0:37:39.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} stole Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s health insurance certificate from her bag in advance,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.33,0:37:44.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and offered to let Saori use her own certificate.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.94,0:37:49.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got her teeth fixed as Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.40,0:37:54.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} killed Saori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and locked her body in the shrine's warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.70,0:37:56.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She set the warehouse on fire later
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.70,0:38:01.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so we'd think Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the victim when we checked her dental records!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.41,0:38:06.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the person with light hair and glasses we saw in the garden...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.00,0:38:07.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.91,0:38:11.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But this is all just guesswork, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.92,0:38:14.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I phoned the dentist to check.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.79,0:38:19.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} he treated had light hair and glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.04,0:38:24.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then Kimie Shimabukuro is still hiding somewhere on this island,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.00,0:38:26.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,waiting for an opportunity to escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.65,0:38:29.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright then, I'll have this entire island searched from top to bottom!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.02,0:38:30.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.90,0:38:32.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.38,0:38:34.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is right here in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.26,0:38:36.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.20,0:38:38.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where? Where is she?!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.59,0:38:40.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.57,0:38:43.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see her anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.66,0:38:45.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, don't you, Rokuro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.53,0:38:50.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kimie's make-up skills were good enough to win her a gold medal.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.06,0:38:51.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.06,0:38:54.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying she's disguised herself as somebody?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.73,0:38:57.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a movie. It wouldn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.34,0:39:01.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, it's hard to pull off a perfect disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.63,0:39:07.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But what if it's someone who doesn't show herself to others very much?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.64,0:39:13.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And what if the only time everyone sees her is at the festival, when she has on very heavy make-up?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.00,0:39:15.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now your choices have been narrowed down significantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.80,0:39:19.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's... impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.20,0:39:23.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But her height...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.02,0:39:25.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Think back.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.02,0:39:30.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember that strange body you found three years ago in the remains of the old warehouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.09,0:39:33.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The one missing its bones from the waist down,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.44,0:39:37.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the locals said it was a mermaid's body?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.67,0:39:45.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was probably the body of a woman whose legs had been bent and tied behind her.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.52,0:39:51.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If my deduction is correct, that woman was Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.04,0:39:51.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.04,0:39:57.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She took over the Lady Mikoto role from my grandmother,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.53,0:40:00.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and kept performing it for the islanders.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.80,0:40:05.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the sad end of a pitiful woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.10,0:40:06.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kimie?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.35,0:40:24.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed, Mr. Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.12,0:40:27.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was pretty confident about this make-up job.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.50,0:40:30.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was that time when we found that the notebook was missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.25,0:40:33.77,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Maybe the ol' lady took it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.77,0:40:34.99,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.77,0:40:39.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said that without even thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.90,0:40:41.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.36,0:40:45.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But when we were talking to Lady Mikoto, we heard Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.80,0:40:49.10,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Great-Grandma! Your bath's ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.59,0:40:53.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that? I recorded it on tape and played it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.45,0:40:56.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why, Kimie?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.65,0:40:59.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The three of them and you have been friends since you were kids!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.10,0:41:04.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That wasn't enough to stop me from avenging my mother's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.14,0:41:08.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That fire at the warehouse three years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.07,0:41:09.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.33,0:41:12.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't win an arrow at the festival,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.09,0:41:14.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so they got drunk and set the warehouse on fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.54,0:41:19.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after seeing my mother, disguised as Lady Mikoto, go inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.04,0:41:21.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess they wanted to see if she really {\i1}was{\i0} immortal.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.00,0:41:26.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Saori panicked and told me the whole story recently,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.96,0:41:29.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the week after she lost her arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.55,0:41:34.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I thought your mother died five years ago while she was out fishing...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.97,0:41:37.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She'd been playing Lady Mikoto for a while, and my make-up job was getting better.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.07,0:41:40.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We decided to fake her death so she'd only have to play one role.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.48,0:41:46.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why didn't you tell us after the fire that it was your mother who died?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.55,0:41:51.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom called me on her cell phone while the flames burned around her...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.00,0:41:54.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kimie... Take care of the people for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.98,0:42:01.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I love this island...so don't let Lady Mikoto die!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.49,0:42:03.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.32,0:42:05.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.79,0:42:08.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know what Saori said after losing her arrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.81,0:42:13.65,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If I can't have another arrow, tell me where the mermaid is buried!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.03,0:42:18.82,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I want to be like Lady Mikoto!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.82,0:42:23.21,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I want to be immortal, so not even a burning building can kill me!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.14,0:42:25.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't forgive them.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.90,0:42:27.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not Toshimi, not Naoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.43,0:42:32.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was easy to get them alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.00,0:42:36.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I just told them I'd show them where the grave was if they won arrows at the festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.25,0:42:38.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Their eyes lit up with excitement.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.45,0:42:41.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The mermaid's grave is my mother's.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.44,0:42:45.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We worked so hard together, all alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.15,0:42:48.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.35,0:42:53.76,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hattori!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.76,0:42:56.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't the only ones who knew the secret of Lady Mikoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.88,0:42:58.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ain't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.99,0:43:05.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That ol' man said this would be the last festival 'cause Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had died.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.07,0:43:07.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I meant...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.07,0:43:08.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.87,0:43:12.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Most of the old folks on the island knew the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.03,0:43:13.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.58,0:43:19.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And we knew it was your mother who died in that fire three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.62,0:43:25.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After the fire, we talked it over and decided to tell you to end the festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.68,0:43:30.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But after seeing you disguised as Lady Mikoto,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.81,0:43:33.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,we couldn't bring ourselves to say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.87,0:43:38.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, this is Mermaid Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.29,0:43:41.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you wanted to continue Lady Mikoto...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.57,0:43:45.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We decided to keep quiet, and help whenever we could...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.95,0:43:49.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We know you did it for the island. We're sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.27,0:43:51.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive us, Kimie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.95,0:43:56.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No... No...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.06,0:43:59.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why couldn't you have told me before?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.45,0:44:04.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you guys needed to snap out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.51,0:44:08.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Immortality ain't nothin' but a nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.79,0:44:11.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Life's valuable 'cause it's short.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.97,0:44:16.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We gotta do our best with the time we got.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.93,0:44:20.11,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Right, Kazuha?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.85,0:44:28.24,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}In the morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.24,0:44:34.65,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}everybody from the island came out to see Kimie{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10} off to the Fukui police station.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.65,0:44:38.49,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But a storm at sea stopped the ship from leaving,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.63,0:44:43.40,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}as if refusing to part with the shrine maiden who had supported the island alone
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.45,0:44:45.86,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}for three long years.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.99,0:46:21.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, show me the wound!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.52,0:46:23.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What's gotten into you?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.50,0:46:25.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Come on...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.59,0:46:28.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the wound of love that Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} marked you with!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.75,0:46:30.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.66,0:46:32.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.66,0:46:34.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The scab had already come off when I woke up this mornin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.65,0:46:36.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all healed up now.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.65,0:46:39.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.99,0:46:42.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I should've stabbed you deeper...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.40,0:46:43.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.22,0:46:46.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm glad your hand's better.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.29,0:46:50.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I don't have to listen to you whine about it anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.90,0:46:53.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.10,0:46:56.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That dope.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.55,0:46:59.20,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}She got me all fired up back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.20,0:47:01.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'm never...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.73,0:47:06.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'm never gonna let anything happen to that girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.90,0:47:12.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Quit trying to look tough.
